tury immigration to Israel (1949-1959)The following chapters discuss the social, cultural and legal contexts of this reality of female illiteracy in the Jewish community—a community that placed a supreme value on male education. The discussion focuses on the patriarchal order and the postulations, rules, norms, sanctions and mythologies that, in antiquity and the Middle Ages, laid the religious foundations of this discriminatory reality.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJewish womenxEducationxHistory. 0aJewish womenxHistory. 0aJewish womenxSocial conditions. 4aErziehung. 4aFamilie, jüdische. 4aFrauengeschichte. 4aGendergeschichte. 4aJüdische Geschichte. 7aHISTORY / Women .2bisacsh  aJewish history.  aJewish women.  adiscriminatory laws.  aenforced illiteracy.  apatriarchal order.1 aSermoneta-Gertel, Shmuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831110445210 cprintz978311104277040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311104391340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111043913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111043913/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb202